Which of the following describes the amount of information that may be broadcasted over a connection?


Hotspot

BSSID

Bandwidth :
    Amount of information that may be broadcasted over a connection.

    Usually, a bandwidth refers to the
                rate of data transfer.

    The unit of measuring the bandwidth is
                bits (amount of data) per second (bps).

Association

