Which of the following is considered as a token to identify
      a 802.11 (Wi-Fi) network
      (by default it is the part of the frame header sent over
          a wireless local area network (WLAN))?


Access Point

SSID : True

Human-readable text string with a maximum length of 32 bytes.
The SSID is a token to identify an 802.11 (Wi-Fi) network; by default,

    Part of the frame header sent over a wireless local area network (WLAN).

Acts as a single shared identifier between the
    AP & clients.
If the SSID of the network is changed,
  reconfiguration of the SSID on every host is required,
    as every user of the network
        configures the SSID into their system.


Hotspot

Association

