Which of the following networks is used for very long-distance communication?


WiMax : TRUE

      IEEE 802.16 standard is a wireless communications standard designed
          to provide multiple
              - physical layer (PHY)
              - media access control (MAC) options.
      Known as WiMax.
      Standard is a specification for
                  fixed broadband wireless metropolitan access networks (MANs)
                            that use a point-to-multipoint architecture.
      It has a range of 1609.34 – 9656.06 kilometers (1–6 miles).

Bluetooth

Wi-Fi

ZigBee

